COLOR ARRAY LOGIC ADDED IN COLORCHANGE.HTML
How it works (quick explanation)
Math.random() * colors.length
‚Üí gives a random number between 0 and array length

Math.floor(...)
‚Üí turns it into a valid array index

colors[randomIndex]
‚Üí selects a random color


creating a list (array)
const colors = ['yellow', 'red', 'blue', 'green', 'purple'];
An array is a list of values.
they all get indexed
0	yellow
1	red
2	blue
3	green
4	purple
Important:Arrays start counting at 0, not 1
Why const? const means:‚ÄúThis variable will not be replaced with something else.‚Äù
